Movistar Argentina Deploys Oracle Corp's Acme Packet SIP Connectivity Solution
Wednesday, 30 Oct 2013 08:00am EDT
Oracle Corp announced that Movistar Argentina, a subsidiary of theTelefonica Group and one of the mobile service providers in Argentina, has deployed Oracle's Acme Packet Net-Net Session Director session border controllers (SBCs) to help enable secure and reliable SIP-based communications. Movistar Argentina implemented Oracle's Acme Packet Net-Net SessionDirector to protect and control its network borders and SIP infrastructure. The solution helps Movistar Argentina enable secure and reliable communications by encrypting signaling and media flows, helping protect the operator's infrastructure against malicious attacks and service overloads and providing load balancing and quality-of-service based routing functions. Oracle's Acme Packet Net-Net Session Director helps Movistar Argentina simplify service deployment by enabling direct interoperability between the operator's various SIP-based platforms, including softswitch, voicemail and communications services elements. The project extended the use of Oracle's Acme Packet Net-Net SessionDirector technology within Movistar Argentina. The operator has been using Oracle's Acme Packet Net-Net Session Director solutions for peering and session routing since 2008 and is well versed in the product's functional and performance advantages.Â 
